amarantin
=========

`amarantin` is a small C++/ROOT library plus one CLI for building ROOT sample
containers from text lists of input ROOT files.

Build
-----

The project now uses CMake.

Standard out-of-source build:

```bash
cmake -S . -B build -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release
cmake --build build --parallel
```

To install into a local prefix:

```bash
cmake -S . -B build -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=$PWD/install
cmake --build build --parallel
cmake --install build
```

You can also disable the application and build only the library:

```bash
cmake -S . -B build -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release -DAMARANTIN_BUILD_APP=OFF
cmake --build build --parallel
```

Environment
-----------

This repository expects:

- C++17 compiler
- CMake >= 3.16
- ROOT
- SQLite3 development files

On the intended uBooNE/Fermilab stack:

```bash
source ./.setup.sh
```

If ROOT is not discovered automatically, set `ROOT_DIR` to the directory
containing `ROOTConfig.cmake`, or ensure `root-config` is on `PATH`.

Docker
------

A portable container build path is included:

```bash
docker build -t amarantin-dev .
docker run --rm -it -v "$PWD":/work -w /work amarantin-dev
```

Then inside the container:

```bash
cmake -S . -B build -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release
cmake --build build --parallel
```

CLI
---

The main executable is `mk_sample`:

```bash
build/bin/mk_sample [--run-db <path>] <output.root> <input.list> [origin] [variation] [beam] [polarity]
```

If `--run-db` is not provided, the library uses:

1. `AMARANTIN_RUN_DB` if it is set
2. `/exp/uboone/data/uboonebeam/beamdb/run.db` otherwise

Repository layout
-----------------

`io/`
  Main library sources and headers

`app/`
  CLI entry point for `mk_sample`

`tools/`
  Helper scripts such as sample-list generation

`cmake/`
  Installed package config template for downstream CMake consumers
